x4freetext: Oxides or oxalates of natural Ho-165, enriched Er-164,
Er-166, Er-167 were adhered to aluminium by
electrophoresis or deposited as a flocculent
suspension in water into aluminium foil boats.
Targets were covered with aluminium foils and
stacked. After irradiation, the oxalate target was
baked to form the oxide. All oxide targets were
weighed, dissolved in acid, heated to dryness and
dissolved in water. Then ytterbium and thulium
activities were separated by an ion-exchange method.
